text.section:
The Attorney General shall prepare a pamphlet of not more than two (2) pages explaining to victims and witnesses of crime:
How the criminal justice system functions from the point of the complaint through the trial;
The role of the attorney for the Commonwealth;
The role of the defense attorney and whether the victim or witness must talk to the defense attorney and under what conditions;
The process for applying for crime victim compensation money;
The duties of the attorney for the Commonwealth under KRS 421.500;
How the victim or witness can be notified of the release of a person from a juvenile detention facility, jail, or prison;
General information on how the victim or witness can protect himself from intimidation; and
Such other information as the Attorney General deems relevant.
